The paper discusses the process of transforming unusable data to support AI algorithm development and deployment, which is a core aspect of data management and analysis. This suggests that cs.DB (Databases) is a likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on the mathematical foundations of data translation and analysis optimization, which aligns with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of associative arrays to describe tabular structures and set mathematics further supports these sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions matrix operations and inference/training calculations used by neural networks, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the discussion of pivot tables and data analysis tools suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a possible sub-category.
